The All Progressives Congress (APC), Ukwa West local government area chapter, Abia state, has distributed palliatives to their members, as part of its efforts to cushion the effect of the Covid-19 pandemic. The palliative items, which ranged from bags of rice to face-masks, were given to the vulnerable members of the party across the ten political wards in the local government area. Speaking on the occasion, the chairman of the Ukwa West APC Covid-19 palliative committee, Mr. ThankGod Ntaku, expressed his appreciation, on behalf of the committee, to the APC leaders in the LGA that supported the project. He stressed that the invaluable cooperation and financial contribution of APC chieftain and leader, Chief Sir Marc Inyanagbo Wabara, was largely responsible for the success of the project. He highlighted the importance of unity and good leadership in any organisation, adding that a more united party in the local government would have resulted in more palliative items to the members. Ntaku, also, attributed the great success achieved to the dedication and commitment of the members of palliative committee, pointing out that the sacrifices they made had further elevated the image of the party in the area. The palliative committee, which had the Abia state APC deputy chairman, Chief Ogunka Adiele John as adviser, was composed of one representative from each of the wards in the local government. Members of the committee include Sebastine Anyasor, secretary; Daberechukwu Ihenko; Barr. Levi Isiguzo and Steve Adindu Nwankwo. Others are; Chief Uche Okeke, Chukwu Ogbuji, Mrs Odochi Onuegbu, Ibe Ememe, Emeka Vincent and Uchenna Nwagbara. Prominent among the donors to the palliative fund were: Chief Ogunka Adiele John, Barr. Evans Omenoge Nwosu, Felix Chinedu Nworgu and Barr. Levi Isiguzo